Results

Shira Salingre

In order to examine the association between species and how this association changes along environmental gradient, I chose three groups of representative fish species: groupers (Epinephelus species + Serranus species), Diplodus species and herbivore species.

MRF models

Association evaluation from MRF model (Clark et al. 1.)

Temperature

# Groupers ----------------------------------------------------------------

MPAs

MPAs are defined as unprotected (enforcement level 0-1) or protected (2-3); therefore this is not a gradient.

Networks comparison

Connectance (Delams et al. 2) is a measure of comparison between networks. Essentially, it describes the level of connectedness of species in the network as a proportion the potential associations in the network:

C0 = [total # of edges] / [total # of nodes^2 (total possible connections)]

L = number of edges (associations) S = number of nodes (species) M = S^2 connectance (C0) = L/M

Temperature models

temp_connect <- tibble(grps_connect = unlist(grps_temp_nested_mod$connectance)) %>% 
  add_column(network = factor(c("low", "medium", "high"))) %>% 
  add_column(dip_connect = unlist(dip_temp_nested_mod$connectance)) %>% 
  add_column(herb_connect = unlist(herb_temp_nested_mod$connectance)) %>% 
  select(network, grps_connect, dip_connect, herb_connect)

formattable(temp_connect)
network grps_connect dip_connect herb_connect
low -0.02962728 0.013876629 0.01819144
medium -0.01400130 0.001991973 -0.02555561
high -0.01552040 -0.616897401 -3.50684614

Relative importance of species association

How much of the model is explained by the occurrence of other species?

Groupers

species temp_model mpa_model depth_model
Epinephelus.costae 0.85159328 0.86146756 0.6029996
Epinephelus.marginatus 0.91355741 0.52804325 0.9179261
Mycteroperca.rubra 0.06798731 0.03060893 0.9518924
Serranus.cabrilla 0.99986911 0.99998747 0.1803659
Serranus.scriba 0.99926372 0.99997678 0.9952475

Most grouper species are affected mainly by other species occurrence rather than covatiates (temperature, MPAs and depth). Mycteroperca rubra shows a different pattern whereas temperature and MPAs are stronger factors than biotic interactions.

Diplodus species are not greatly affected by other species accept Diplodus cervinus, which seem to show a different pattern with temperature and depth effects.
